args: It's so quiet... Hard to believe that just a\nlittle while ago the place was bustling\nwith a party.
What a blast that Halloween was.\n...Hmm?
Ah, Master {player_name}.\nOut for a late-night stroll?
I was having trouble falling asleep.\nMaybe I got overexcited from all the fun\nat the party.
I just wanted to take it all in for a little\nbit longer.
That's certainly not a problem, but please\ndo be sure to get a proper evening's rest.
If you end up oversleeping on account of\nthis little jaunt, it would interfere with\ntomorrow's schedule, after all.
Heh. All right. But what about you?
I am conducting the night patrol.
As we've already had one bunch of thieves\ncreep into the castle, it would be best to\nremain vigilant with our patrols.
Wait, you've been patrolling all this time?!
Look, I'll take care of it from here.\nYou go and get some sleep.
I am quite all right. Please take your own\nrest, Master {player_name}.
You need to account for your own sleep\nand time as we—Ah!
Edward! ...See? I told you that you're\nexhausted.
You gave me a nasty scare, that's what.\nWe were in the middle of talking when\nyou suddenly collapsed.
And me. I heard {player_name}\nshout and came running.
And I brought ya to the closest room,\nwhich happened to be this one.
C'mon, Edward! Who do you think brought\nthat fruit and water from the kitchen?
Even Master Luca went to such trouble?\nAh, but I am truly sorry.
You've nothing to be sorry for, Edward.\nWE'RE sorry for not being more attentive\nto your needs.
Guess we just sorta ended up relyin' on\nya for pretty much everything.
Caring for those around you all the time\nbuilds fatigue. It's really no wonder this\nhappened.
So now you should rest and make up\nfor all the hard work you did for us.\nGot it?
Yes, but what about my work for tomorr—
We got it. You just relax.
I think it's about time for all of us to be\ngetting back to our own rooms.
You'll never be able to rest and recover\nif we continue making noise here.
I'll look after him, so all of you should go\nand get some sleep.
All right. Have a good night,\n{player_name}. You too, Edward.
Master {player_name}...\nI'm truly sorry for this burden.
Collapsing in front of my master is proof\npositive of my inability to care for myself.
And that is in spite of my repeated\nboasts that I was quite all right.\nI truly am sorry.
Really, don't worry about it. ...Although\nI think I've figured out your flaw.
It's that you don't know how to switch\nyourself off and rest.
No. With things as they stand now,\nany explanation I may have will ring\nmost hollow indeed.
You're serious, dedicated, and responsible.\nYou work so hard, which makes it easy to\nrely on and trust you.
But I'd like you to be realistic and not push\nyourself past your limits when things are\nbusy or hard.
I want you to put yourself first from now\non. Practice self-care.
Ah, but I am a disappointing butler.
And that is in spite of the concern you\nshowed for me before.
In the end, I ended up in this unsightly\nstate, quite thoroughly useless to anyone.
What matters is what you do WHEN you\nfail. Don't you agree?
The Edward I know isn't the type to keep\nmaking the same mistakes.
Hmm... Yes, I suppose so. I shall not let\nyou see this unsightly side of me again.
I will do as you've requested and take\na good and proper rest.
Good. That will give me peace of mind.\nI'm still going to be relying on you moving\nforward, you know?
Master {player_name}...\nYour words do me a great honor.
Oh, but if you actually remember to rest\nevery now and then, it means you won't\nhave a flaw anymore.
And yet I've had a weakness all along, sir.
It is my one and only weak point, so I\ncan't breathe a word of it to another soul.
It might be good for me to know about\nit though, as a comrade. ...Actually,\nyou know what? Don't worry about it.
Whatever weaknesses you or I might have,\nwe'll make up for them by sharing our\nstrengths with one another.
I would expect no less than this kind of\nthinking from you. ...My stars and garters!\nLook at the time!
I apologize for commandeering your bed\nfor the entire evening.
It's fine. Keep it for the night.
Are you certain, sir? I am still able to\nwalk and could return to my own—
Keep it, Edward. Sleep in. Wake up late.\nSee what it feels like.
It would appear that I truly am susceptible\nto your words, master.
I shall indeed take a nice long rest.\nThank you, master.
